  "id": "019cdcdc-fd01-7d11-b0d7-b647450cf058",
  "content": "## ChunkingPipeline\n\n### Pipeline Steps\n\n1. **Resolve strategy**: `registry.resolve(meta.extension)` → `Arc<dyn ChunkingStrategy>`\n2. **Domain chunking**: `strategy.chunk(source, meta)` → `Vec<RawChunk>`\n3. **Merge small chunks**: `strategy.merge_small()` if overridden, else kernel default (merge adjacent where sum < max_tokens)\n4. **Enforce token budget**: For each chunk exceeding budget, call `strategy.split_oversized()`. Recurse until all chunks fit.\n5. **Add overlap context**: `strategy.overlap_context()` if overridden, else kernel default (take last N tokens of previous chunk if `overlap_tokens > 0`)\n6. **Build ProcessedChunks**: Attach token estimates, processing info, strategy name.\n\nOrdering rationale: merge before split. Merging first consolidates small chunks; splitting then handles anything still oversized. Avoids splitting a 40-token chunk that would have merged with its neighbor.\n",
  "source_version": "docs/rfcs/2026-03-02-m3.3-embedding-chunking-design.md",
